5:
Happy Holidays! Santa's arrived with
your gifts!
9: We have plenty. Here you go.
14:
What's with those outfits? And that
huge sack?
17:
What do you mean? Santa is Santa,
of course! We deliver gifts to
everyone around the world!
21: Here you go, this one's yours!
27:
Tell Santa what you want! I'll hunt
down whatever treasures you desire!
31:
I must admit, I didn't expect this
particular Palpebran holiday to
make its way into our world.
34:
It's clearly bringing joy to the
people—you have my gratitude for
this, Mia.
38:
I was asking myself just what this
new holiday should celebrate, and
then it hit me—the arrival of Saint
Mia! Whaddya think?
41:
Come on, everyone! Saint Mia will
grant you your wishes! Don't be
intimidated by her tiger-like
appearance—those are just her
Santa Claws, hohoho!
47:
Hey, Santa.
Can we ask for ANYTHING we want?
52:
You bet! No matter how big, you
leave it to me!
56:
What about flowers? Or… maybe a
whole garden?
59:
Flowers don't bloom in
Pandemonium, so fiend children
have never seen them.
63:
Is that true? Flowers don't bloom in
Pandemonium? Like, at ALL?!
67:
I saw one a long time ago, so I
thought it'd be nice if everyone else
could see them too...
72:
A garden, you say? There may be
one in the Silver Woods… The center
is Elf territory, so it shouldn't be too
dangerous.
80:
It's settled then—request accepted!
Treasure Santa is on the case!
83: Say, Stella… I've got an idea!
95:
Tada! Feast your eyes on a bona
fide garden!
98:
Wow, it's... amazing! It's so beautiful...
And it smells great, too!
117:
There are sure to be unseen
treasures buried throughout the
land!
120:
I call upon all of you to become
Treasure Santas yourselves and
uncover all these hidden goodies!
It's ADVENTURE time!
124:
What an incredible sight… One unlike
any I've ever seen.
129:
Thanks for letting me invite
everyone, Regitare!
133:
Needn't be thankin' me, lass! Been a
spell since things were this lively
'round 'ere.
137:
The whole forest is filled with cheer.
Yer free to come on by whenever
you fancy.
142:
Mia... I can't possibly thank you
enough for this!
146: H-huh? What's this all of a sudden?
151:
This world… It might be exactly what
I was looking for! You might have
just saved us, Mia! You're a saint!
154:
Regitare, could you tell me all you
can about this land?
158:
Whaa? I mean, I'm super happy I
could make you happy! Not that I
have any idea what I did, exactly.
163:
Hehe… Happiness is seriously
infectious, isn't it? Spreads from one
person right to the next!
167:
Yeah! And it's all thanks to you,
Santa Mia!
171:
Say, Eric. Isn't there anything that
you want for yourself? Name it and
it's yours!
175: Well... I wanna find my big sisters.
179: They're not my REAL sisters, but...
187:
They're Marly's children. They went
missing a long time ago.
191:
I... I see...
That might be a bit of a tall order...
194:
And... are you sure that's what YOU
want, and not what Marly wants?
198:
I dunno, but if Marly were less lonely,
it'd make me happy.
203:
That just might be the sweetest
thing I've heard all day, Eric!
207:
Well, you don't gotta tell me twice! I'll
do everything I can to find them!
210:
So, um, can you tell me anything
about these kids? Any particular
traits, or their names, maybe?
215: Sure! Their names are Arly and Arum!
220:
Arly and Arum, eh?
Got it!
238:
Yeah! Santa brings everyone
presents, right? And wears red
clothes and rides in a sleigh—
240: And has floofy fur and tiger ears!
247:
Treasure Santa is coming to
town—with presents for all of you!
